<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="95" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="95">
Female can be easily recognized by its large body size (18-22 mm); black body covered with black hairs throughout (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Megachile (Callomegachile) atratiformis Meade-Waldo, 1914, female a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d frontal view of mandible and labrum e dorsal view of mesoscutum f dorsal view of metasoma g lateral view of metasoma and scopa." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.997.34935.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479631" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">2a</figureCitation>
); clypeus without median tubercle; mandibles four teeth; apical margin of labrum truncate without tooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Megachile (Callomegachile) atratiformis Meade-Waldo, 1914, female a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d frontal view of mandible and labrum e dorsal view of mesoscutum f dorsal view of metasoma g lateral view of metasoma and scopa." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.997.34935.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479631" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">2d</figureCitation>
); mesoscutum with weak transverse wrinkle pattern on disc, posteriorly also with weakly transverse wrinkle pattern (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Megachile (Callomegachile) atratiformis Meade-Waldo, 1914, female a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d frontal view of mandible and labrum e dorsal view of mesoscutum f dorsal view of metasoma g lateral view of metasoma and scopa." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.997.34935.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/479631" pageId="0" pageNumber="95">2e</figureCitation>
); yellow wings; black scopa. Male can be easily recognized by the presence of black setae patch on medial cell of forewings; apical of T6 with shallow concavity; front tibia modified (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.101.1182" author="Engel, MS" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="95" pagination="51 - 80" refId="B20" refString="Engel, MS, Gonzalez, VH, 2011. Alocanthedon, a new subgenus of Chalicodoma from Southeast Asia (Hymenoptera, Megachilidae). ZooKeys 101: 51 - 80, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.101.1182" title="Alocanthedon, a new subgenus of Chalicodoma from Southeast Asia (Hymenoptera, Megachilidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.101.1182" volume="101" year="2011">Engel and Gonzalez 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
